HEADWORD: kinetogenesis
<hw>ki*ne`to*gen"e*sis</hw>
<pr>(k⟦isl⟧*n⟦emac⟧`t⟦osl⟧*j⟦ecr⟧n"⟦esl⟧*s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>kinhto`s</grk> movable + E. <ets>genesis</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The doctrine or hypothesis that animal
